# Results & Visual Insights

This section summarizes the main tactical insights extracted from the analysis
of goal kicks performed by Bayer Leverkusen during the 2023/2024 season.

The results focus on decision-making patterns, execution types, and contextual
factors influencing goal kick outcomes.

---

## 1. Goal Kick Distribution by Type

![Goal kick types](figures/goal_kick_types.png)

**Insight:**  
Short goal kicks are the most frequently used option, suggesting a clear tactical
preference for structured build-up from the back rather than direct play.

---

## 2. Pressure Context at Goal Kick Execution

![Pressure context](figures/pressure_context.png)

**Insight:**  
Most goal kicks are executed under low or medium pressure, indicating effective
positional occupation during restarts.

---

## 3. Pass Length vs Tactical Outcome

![Pass length](figures/pass_length_outcome.png)

**Insight:**  
Long goal kicks show higher variability in outcome quality, while short and
medium-length executions tend to produce more stable and predictable results.

---

## 4. Tactical Rule Model Score Distribution

![Rule score](figures/rule_score_distribution.png)

**Insight:**  
The rule-based tactical model discriminates clearly between optimal and suboptimal
goal kick decisions, validating the WHENâ€“HOW framework.

---

## 5. Preferred Target Zones

![Target zones](figures/target_zones.png)

**Insight:**  
Goal kicks are predominantly directed towards wide zones, aligning with modern
positional play principles.
